        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 25 at 1:40PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 140 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ukiah, or 37 miles southeast of Heppner, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Meacham, Hilgard, Lehman Hot Springs, Kamela, and southeastern
Umatilla Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
